The paper deals with lower bounds for testing graph properties and Boolean functions, which are central topics in computer science. The rejection sampling model introduced in the paper is a new model for testing graph properties, which is likely to be classified under cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The lower bounds for tolerant testing of Boolean functions involve concepts from probability theory and information theory, which are relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also uses techniques from graph theory and data structures, which are relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
